<section class="page-hero page-hero--compact">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal" data-reveal>Resources</p>
    <h1 class="display display--sm reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 40ms">Mortgage terms worth knowing</h1>
    <p class="muted reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 80ms">
      Quick reference material from <strong>Sood Mortgages Group</strong>. This is educational context, not personalized advice — your loan officer will confirm how each concept applies to your file.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="container resources-split">
    <div class="faq-grid">
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal open>
      <summary>What is a Loan Estimate (LE)?</summary>
      <p class="muted">A standardized disclosure that outlines key terms, projected payments, and closing costs. It helps you compare offers on an apples-to-apples basis within the regulatory timing window.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 40ms">
      <summary>Rate vs. APR — why both appear</summary>
      <p class="muted">The interest rate is the cost of borrowing the principal. The APR includes certain fees and prepaid finance charges expressed as an annual percentage, which can make it easier to compare total cost across lenders.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 80ms">
      <summary>Debt-to-income (DTI) in plain terms</summary>
      <p class="muted">Lenders compare your monthly obligations (housing, debts, some installment items) to your qualifying monthly income. We review DTI early so you understand how a car payment or student loan affects purchasing power.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 120ms">
      <summary>Pre-approval vs. pre-qualification</summary>
      <p class="muted">Pre-qualification is often a lighter review. Pre-approval typically involves documented income and assets so sellers and listing agents take your offer more seriously.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 160ms">
      <summary>What happens at closing?</summary>
      <p class="muted">You sign final loan and title documents, funds are disbursed per the settlement statement, and ownership transfers (purchase) or your new loan replaces the old one (refinance). We walk you through the Closing Disclosure beforehand.</p>
    </details>
    </div>
    <aside class="resources-aside reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 60ms" data-parallax="subtle">
      <figure class="media-frame">
        <img
          src="<%= images.resources %>"
          alt="Books on shelves — educational mortgage resources and reference"
          width="1200"
          height="900"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>
      <p class="muted small" style="margin-top: 0.75rem">Placeholder photography ships with the site for reliable loading; swap for your own photography when ready.</p>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--muted">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal" data-reveal>
      <h2 class="section-title">First-time buyer checklist</h2>
      <p class="muted narrow-inline">Gather these items early — your file moves faster when the story is complete from day one.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="checklist-grid">
      <ul class="checklist card checklist-block reveal" data-reveal>
        <li>Government-issued ID for all borrowers</li>
        <li>Last 30 days of pay stubs (or P&amp;L if self-employed)</li>
        <li>W-2s or 1099s for the last two tax years</li>
        <li>Two months of bank statements — all pages</li>
      </ul>
      <ul class="checklist card checklist-block reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 50ms">
        <li>Most recent quarterly asset statements for retirement accounts</li>
        <li>Landlord history or rent payment documentation if applicable</li>
        <li>Gift letter template if down payment includes gift funds</li>
        <li>Purchase contract and MLS sheet once you are under contract</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container split split--flip">
    <figure class="media-frame reveal" data-reveal data-parallax="subtle">
      <img
        src="<%= images.homeClosing %>"
        alt="Keys and closing — preparing for settlement day"
        width="1000"
        height="667"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />
    </figure>
    <div class="reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 60ms">
      <h2 class="section-title">Appraisal, title, and insurance — how they fit together</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        <strong>Appraisal</strong> establishes value for the lender. <strong>Title</strong> confirms ownership and lien position. <strong>Hazard insurance</strong> protects the collateral. Delays in any leg can push closing — we help you see dependencies early.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        When value comes in below contract price, or when repairs appear on an inspection report, we discuss financing options with your agent before you waive contingencies.
      </p>
      <a class="text-link" href="/contact?topic=Closing%20timeline%20question">Ask about your closing timeline →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container cta-band reveal" data-reveal>
    <div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Questions beyond this list?</h2>
      <p class="muted">Send us a note — we answer in business context, not generic boilerplate.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/contact?topic=Resource%20question">Ask a question</a>
  </div>
</section>
